                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/1799: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-09-19T20:00:00+08:00"
                            >September 19, 1931—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 19—10:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>606. Following telegram has been received from Langdon<note n="22"
                        xml:id="d15fn22">William R. Langdon, Consul at Dairen.</note> at Dairen.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“September 19, 2 p.m. Consul at Mukden telephones for repetition to you that
                        Japanese took over whole of Mukden at 1 a.m., this morning; they have also
                        occupied Changchun, Antung and Newchwang and are running public services at
                        all these places. Foreigners are all safe.”</p>
                </quote>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
